main event: A civilian reported observing a cloud-like object moving at high speed across the sky in San Diego, California, on January 8, 1967.
interesting points: The witness initially thought it was an airplane but noticed it was changing shape and direction., The object was described as having a dull glow and being indistinct., The witness observed the object for about 30 minutes before it suddenly disappeared., The report was submitted to Project Blue Book for further investigation., The witness experienced skepticism from those they told about the sighting.
witness description: A civilian who observed the object from a window.
